cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on analyzing both linguistic and deep image features of fashion brands' social media posts on Twitter and Instagram. This falls under the scope of multimedia analysis.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper explores how fashion brands use social media platforms to reach out to their customers and obtain feedback on their products. This falls under the scope of social and information networks.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper analyzes the linguistic features of fashion brands' social media posts on Twitter and Instagram. This falls under the scope of computation and language.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the impact of social media on fashion brand marketing and how it affects consumers. This falls under the scope of computers and society.
- cs.SD (Software Development): The paper may involve the development of software tools or algorithms for analyzing social media data. This falls under the scope of software development.
